    <description>"Eww, that's dirty!" \n "Do you think so? Well, I guess I'd better not show you where the lemonade is made..." \n \n Hard liquor is defined as any alcoholic beverage created by distilling ethanol using fruits or vegetables that have already been separately fermented. In this case, lemons are used. Hard liquors have significantly higher rates of ethanol than drinks such as beer or wine. \n \n As has been consistently stated and even sung, don't ask where the lemonade is made. Some of its sources are benign, but others...</description>
